High level of streptomycin resistance (MIC 4,096 mg/L) exhibited in Y. pestis S19960127 due to a rpsL mutation associated with substitution of amino-acid 43 of ribosomal protein S12. Sequence comparison showed no amino-acid alteration at position 88 of ribosomal protein S12 or rrs gene mutations in S19960127.
